Local Void and Dipole Misalignment} PUH v6 interprets the Local Void/Bubble as a time differential effect, where low-mass regions run faster time (γ ≈ 1) than dense galaxies (γ < 1), creating shear that expands the void without supernovae. This modulates the CMB dipole (370 km/s toward Leo) and Quasar dipole (1700 km/s toward galactic center, ~90° offset, ~4.5x stronger), with void shear amplifying quasar signals via lattice asymmetry. The 6° hotspot aligns with the galactic center, explaining misalignment. Benchmark with Quaia DR1 catalogs (arXiv:2508.20769) quantifies residuals.
